article.headline: Wagner 66, Albany 65
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Mark Porter's layup with 1 second left gave Wagner a 66-65 victory over Albany on Saturday. Porter finished with eight points on 4-of-6 shooting. Sean Munson had 21 points and 16 rebounds to lead the Seahawks (1-2), while Jamal Smith added 10 points. Lucious Jordan, who finished with 13 points, hit a 3-pointer with 1:07 remaining to give Albany a 65-64 lead. Kirsten Zoellner and Jamar Wilson each had 10 points for the Great Danes (2-1), who trailed 35-34 at halftime. Jordan scored 10 of his points in a 23-9 run that put Albany on top 57-44 midway through the second half. The Seahawks responded with a 16-5 surge to move within 62-60 on Smith's jumper with 3:17 left.
